The Lagos Chamber of Commerce and Industry (LCCI) yesterday inducted 75 new members into its community. The chamber during its maiden virtual induction ceremony described the decision of the new members to join LCCI as a strategic one that would add value to their businesses. According to the president of the chamber, Mrs. Toki Mabogunje, LCCI is a special place and a business community filled with exceptional business leaders and top corporate executives across all sectors of the economy. She described the chamber as a leading voice in the promotion of private sector interests to facilitate the global competitiveness of the Nigeria economy. “As we formally accept your organisation into the Lagos chamber community, I wish to underline the commitment of the chamber to the cherished tradition of high ethical standards, integrity and good corporate governance in business practice. As businessmen and women, we have obligations which transcend profit making. We should pay adequate attention to the integrity of our business transactions and practices,” she said. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here  LCCI elects Ruwase as new President Segun Alabi is LCCI’s new image maker LCCI signs MoU with Oxford Business Group on ‘Nigeria 2020’